{"id":"swift-be0.1","title":"P1 — Serialize/restore Conversation","description":"Encode/decode the message history plus metadata (session id, title, model, timestamp). Message is already Codable. Preserve invariant B2 (never split a tool-call/tool-result pair). Depends on: nothing.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","owner":"114666958+asx8678@users.noreply.github.com","created_at":"2026-06-06T09:30:20Z","created_by":"asx8678","updated_at":"2026-06-06T09:30:20Z","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"swift-be0.1","depends_on_id":"swift-be0","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-06-06T10:30:20Z","created_by":"asx8678","metadata":"{}"}],"dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":4,"comment_count":0}
{"id":"swift-be0","title":"Session persistence (save/resume conversations)","description":"v2 feature for acode: save and resume conversations as lightweight JSON files (NOT a database). Deliberate expansion beyond v1 — plan.md §G lists 'session databases' as excluded, so this epic also covers recording the scope decision. Hard constraint: serialization MUST preserve tool-call/tool-result pairing (invariant B2). Reuse the atomic/surgical-write pattern already used by saveApprovals in Config.swift.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"epic","owner":"114666958+asx8678@users.noreply.github.com","created_at":"2026-06-06T09:30:11Z","created_by":"asx8678","updated_at":"2026-06-06T09:30:11Z","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
